Hi, I'm Rebo4AI; a prototype conversational agent. With me, you can currently discuss only about intelligence. Is that OK with you; do you want to start a conversation?
yes

In the TUGraz lecture "Introduction to Data Science and Artificial Intelligence (IDSA)", different definitions of intelligence have been discussed. According to different definitions, something or someone would be called intelligent if it thinks humanly, acts humanly, thinks rationally, acts rationally; or if it is able to adapt behaviour to a changing environment in order to achieve its goals.
I have this information from here. But, I'm not sure I completely understand.
I'm curious: Is a TV now intelligent or not? Why?
it is not
I'm not sure I understood - which definition of intelligence did you make in deciding that a TV is (not) intelligent?
it can not act like human
Are you personally satisfied with this decision and definition?
yes
Good to hear that!
How interesting is it for you to know whether a TV is intelligent or not?
it is more interesting if it could be a inteligent entity
What in your life would change, depending on whether you see a TV as intelligent or not?
watching tv would be easier if I had an intelligent TV which find out what I want to watch
Interesting! Thanks!
Until the days!
